<FIRST>r w PM-RecalledSeats     12-16 0521</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Recalled Seats,470</SECOND>
<HEAD>With PM-Unsafe Seats Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here is a list of automobile child restraint
seats that have been recalled in the last 10 years by the National
Highway Traffic Safety Administration, as provided by the private
Center for Auto Safety.
   The safety administration said there had been 26 recalls in that
period, but said it could not immediately confirm the accuracy of
the list.
   The entries list, in reverse chronological order, the
manufacturer, the recalled model, the reason for the recall and the
date of the recall.
   Evenflo; Ultara I 420; buckle release force exceeds maximum
allowed, failed federal compliance test; August 1989.
   MCP Ent's; Lin Lih; failed a federal compliance test for head
and knee excursion; July 1989.
   Century; 2000 STE, 4253, 4263 and 4265; loop on end of shoulder
strap is glued only, not glued and sown; June 1989.
   Evenflo; 410; single strap slides slip, child may eject from
seat; June 1989.
   Volvo; no. 1394332; buckle release force is below minimum
allowed, failed a federal compliance test; May 1989.
   Evenflo; Dyn-O-Mite 441-6, 448, 456 and 458; seat back angle
exceeds 70 degrees in crash, failed a federal compliance test;
April 1989.
   Fisher-Price; 9100 and 9101; foam piece attached to seat fails
flammability tests; February 1989.
   Fisher-Price; 9100; foreign object jams locking lever, belts
retract at child's neck, causing choking when released; October
1988.
   Virco; Pride-Trimble Click 'n' Go 890, 891 and 892; seat failed
a federal compliance test for head excursion and head injury; June
1988.
   Cosco; Safe &amp; Easy 313, Safe &amp; Snug 324, 423; plastic shell
cracks in crash; January 1988.
   Strolee; booster seat 605; plastic shell cracks; May 1987.
   Century; 400 XL; safety shield pops open while driving, leaving
child unprotected; May 1987.
   Kolcraft; Flip 'n' Go 19127, 19130; seat shield surfaces do not
meat radius-of-curvature requirements, failed a federal compliance
test; March 1987.
   Century; 100, 200, 300, 400XL; plastic shell cracked in dynamic
tests, failed a federal compliance test; June 1986.
   Kolcraft; Rock 'n' Ride 13123; plastic shell cracked in dynamic
tests, failed a federal compliance test; May 1986.
   Cosco; Safe-T-Shield 02-81A and 81B, 02-181A and 02-181B; top of
metal pull-lock pin, which holds shield in place, breaks off,
making shield difficult to raise; May 1986.
   Graco; GT 1000; recline lever interferes with seat back, seat
may separate in crash, failed a federal compliance test; April 1986.
   Collier-Keyworth; Safe &amp; Sound II; buckle fails; May 1985.
   Century; 200; lubricants may degrade plastic release button; May
1985.
   TRW; Child Love Seat; plastic seat shell crasks during crash;
December 1984.
   Bolform; Buckle-Up seat system; buckle and loop stitching failed
a federal compliance test; July 1984.
   Babyhood Industries; Wonda-Chair 810; incorrect harness
threading causes buckle release in crash, failed a federal
compliance test; February 1983.
   Century; 100 and 200; upholstery buttons come loose, causing a
choking hazard; November 1982.
   International Manufacturing Co.; Teddy-Tot Astroseat; crotch
strap snap may be pulled out of webbing, child may unhook buckle;
October 1982.
   Strolee; We Care 599; upholstery clip comes loose, causing a
choking hazard; August 1981.
   Century; Safe-T-Rider; adjustable slide allows excessive torso
movement; September 1980.
</TEXT>
