<HEAD>Jet Blasts Out Restaurant Window, Diners Injured</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A blast from the engines of a private jet
shattered the window of a restaurant and showered the diners with
shards, slightly injuring 15 people, police said.
   The Gulfstream 3 executive jet moved to within about 20 yards of
the Copacabana restaurant at Lindbergh Field as it positioned
itself for takeoff Friday night. When it departed, the engine
acceleration produced a wind blast that broke a large glass window,
police Sgt. Dave Douglas said.
   ``The people in there were showered with the broken glass,''
Douglas said.
   Of the injured, eight were transported to hospitals and the rest
treated at the scene. Douglas said most of the injuries involved
cuts or twisted ankles.
