<HEAD>Sketch Brings 400 Tips on Missing Boy</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. CLOUD, Minn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Investigators looking for a boy who was
kidnapped in October were deluged with tips after they released a
new sketch of a suspect.
   More than 400 people called a special task force on the
abduction of Jacob Wetterling Friday, said FBI Agent Byron Gigler.
   ``Hopefully we can put a name to this guy,'' he said.
   Gigler said most of calls were from the St. Joseph area, where
11-year-old Jacob lived. Some tipsters provided names, telephone
numbers and addresses of people they said closely resembled the man
in the sketch.
   The sketch was released Thursday during a news conference in
which investigators said they believed the man who kidnapped Jacob
was also responsible for the January abduction and sexual assault
on a boy in Cold Spring.
