<HEAD>Boy Believed Missing Sleeps Through Police Search</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAMPA, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 6-year-old boy reported missing when he
didn't return home from school apparently was asleep Saturday in
the back of a bus the whole time police searched for him on the
ground and by helicopter.
   Glen S. Bacon was still snoozing when officers found him
stretched out in the back of a Boys Club bus at about 3:30 a.m.
Saturday, said police Lt. T.A. Kessler.
   The first-grader usually takes the bus to the Interbay Boys Club
each day after school. When the boy's grandmother went to pick him
up early Friday evening, she learned he had never arrived.
   Police launched a search that included using the department's
helicopter and going door-to-door in the neighborhood where Glen
lives.
   ``He apparently fell asleep on his way to the boy's club,''
Kessler said. ``He was scrunched down, so at first it looked like
the bus was empty.''
   After a whole night of searching, an officer decided to
backtrack.
   ``They found him,'' Kessler said. ``He slept through the whole
thing.''
