<HEAD>MOUNTAIN BROOK, Ala.: authorities said.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Eleventh U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals Judge Robert S. Vance,
58, ``was killed at his Mountain Brook residence about three
o'clock this afternoon by an explosive device,'' U.S. Attorney
Frank Donaldson said in Birmingham.
   State Attorney General Don Siegelman told staff members in
Montgomery that initial reports indicated a mail bomb was involved,
said Assistant Attorney General Don Valeska.
   However, Siegelman said the blast remained under investigation
and no firm details were immediately available, according to
Valeska.
   Siegelman told staff members to ``dedicate every resource of
this office to find the perpetrators.''
